<nav class="nav" id="nav" data-screen-label="Nav"><svg class="sunmark" viewBox="0 0 32 32" aria-hidden="true"><circle class="sun-disc" cx="16" cy="16" r="10"></circle></svg><a class="wm" href="/">AMPM <small>BUILDING SERVICES</small></a><div class="links"><a href="/services/" class="">Services</a><a href="/work/" class="">Work</a><a href="/compliance/" class="active">Compliance</a><a href="/about/" class="">About</a><a href="/contact/" class="">Contact</a></div><a class="phone" href="tel:03300430080">0330 043 0080</a></nav><div class="page"><div class="shell"><section class="sec p-hero"><div class="reveal in"><div class="kicker">Compliance &amp; Building Safety</div></div><h1 class="reveal d1 in">Built on the<br>golden thread.</h1><p class="lede reveal d2 in">The Building Safety Act changed what a credible contractor has to prove. We were built for it — inheriting <strong>Gemini AMPM's life-safety discipline since 1997</strong>, so the golden thread and audit-ready handover are the default, not an upgrade.</p></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">The golden thread, our method</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Information that survives handover.</h2></div><div class="thread reveal in"><div class="step"><span class="n">01</span><h4>Capture</h4><p>Every design decision, product and certificate recorded from day one — not reconstructed at handover.</p></div><div class="step"><span class="n">02</span><h4>Coordinate</h4><p>One accountable team holds the information across all four service lines, on the Group operating stack.</p></div><div class="step"><span class="n">03</span><h4>Verify</h4><p>RAMS, method statements and inspection records checked against the audit posture used on Higher-Risk Buildings.</p></div><div class="step"><span class="n">04</span><h4>Hand over</h4><p>An audit-ready, structured information set the client and their PQQ teams can actually use.</p></div></div></section><section class="sec"><div class="intro2 reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 36px;"><div><div class="kicker">Accreditations</div><h2 class="dhead">The accreditations<br>we operate under.</h2></div><p class="body">AMPM Building Services is a young company. Today it operates under the accreditations held across <strong>AMPM Group</strong> &mdash; largely through our sister company <strong>Gemini AMPM</strong> &mdash; rather than in its own name, and sends the full certificate pack with every PQQ response. Our own management systems are in build (below).</p></div><p class="body" style="margin-bottom: 14px;"><strong>Held at AMPM Group level (primarily through Gemini AMPM) &mdash; not currently held in the name of AMPM Building Services:</strong></p><div class="acc-wall reveal in"><div class="cell"><span class="t">CHAS Elite</span><span class="d">SSIP &middot; H&amp;S pre-qual</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="t">Constructionline Gold</span><span class="d">Supply-chain / PQ</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="t">SafeContractor</span><span class="d">SSIP approved</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="t">Avetta</span><span class="d">SSIP / supply-chain</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="t">Cyber Essentials</span><span class="d">Cyber security</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="t">BESA</span><span class="d">Building engineering</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="t">FPA</span><span class="d">Fire Protection Assoc.</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="t">British Safety Council</span><span class="d">H&amp;S membership</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="t">FIA</span><span class="d">Fire Industry Assoc.</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="t">BAFE</span><span class="d">Fire-safety registered</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="t">NSI Gold</span><span class="d">Security systems</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="t">FIRAS</span><span class="d">Passive-fire install</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="t">CleanDucts</span><span class="d">Ductwork hygiene</span></div></div><p class="body" style="margin-top: 16px; font-size: 0.9em; color: var(--ink-3);">These accreditations are held by AMPM Group / Gemini AMPM. AMPM Building Services operates under them and applies them to projects delivered under the Group&rsquo;s contracting structure; it does not yet hold them in its own name.</p><div class="reveal in" style="margin-top: 40px; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); padding-top: 32px;"><div class="kicker">Working towards our own</div><h3 class="dhead sm" style="margin: 10px 0 14px;">Our own IMS, in build.</h3><p class="body">AMPM Building Services is building its own integrated management system (IMS) aligned to <strong>ISO 9001</strong> (Quality), <strong>ISO 14001</strong> (Environmental) and <strong>ISO 45001</strong> (Health &amp; Safety), with the intention of seeking UKAS-accredited certification in due course. AMPM Building Services is <strong>not currently certified</strong> to any of these standards &mdash; until certificates are awarded in our own name, we operate under the Group accreditations above.</p></div></section></div><section class="band ink" data-nav-dark="true"><div class="shell"><div class="intro2 reveal in"><div><div class="kicker on-dark">Inherited credibility</div><h2 class="dhead sm" style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">A quarter-century<br>of life-safety behind us.</h2></div><div><p class="body" style="color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.86);">Our sister company <strong style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Gemini AMPM</strong> has protected the South East's most demanding buildings — fire, security and passive fire — since 1997. Employee-owned, with NSI Gold, BAFE, FIRAS and Constructionline Gold among its accreditations.</p><p class="body" style="color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.86); margin-top: 14px;">For Building Services clients, that means the compliance posture, the audit framework and the operating stack are the Group's — not a new contractor's first attempt at them.</p><div class="cta-row2"><a class="btn ghost" href="https://geminiampm.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Visit Gemini AMPM ↗</a></div></div></div></div></section><section class="band green" data-nav-dark="true"><div class="shell"><div class="cta-split reveal in"><div><div class="kicker on-dark">For PQQ teams</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Request our<br>compliance pack.</h2><p class="body" style="margin-top: 18px;">Accreditation certificates, insurance schedule, RAMS templates and our golden-thread method statement — sent to a named contact.</p></div><div class="cta-row2" style="flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start;"><a class="btn ghost" href="/contact/">Request the pack →</a><a class="btn ghost" href="/contact/">General enquiry</a></div></div></div></section></div><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 28px;"><div class="kicker">FAQs</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Compliance questions,<br>answered.</h2></div><div class="faq reveal in"><details class="faq-item"><summary>Are you accredited?</summary><p>AMPM Building Services works under the accreditations held across AMPM Group — the standards and certifications built over the Group’s 29-year history. We provide the relevant certificates and PQQ evidence on request.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>What is the “golden thread”, and how do you maintain it?</summary><p>The golden thread is the digital record of a building’s safety information — kept accurate and accessible from design through to handover and occupation, as required for higher-risk buildings under the Building Safety Act 2022. We hand over O&amp;M manuals, as-builts and test records as a structured, lasting set.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Do you work under CDM 2015?</summary><p>Yes. Every project is delivered under the Construction (Design and Management) Regulations 2015 — with the duty-holder roles, risk management and documentation that demands.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Can you complete our PQQ or pre-qualification?</summary><p>Yes. We hold capability statements, insurances, method statements, accreditations and references ready for PQQ and pre-qualification submissions to Tier-1 main contractors and direct clients.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>How do you handle fire and building-safety compliance?</summary><p>Fire-stopping, compartmentation and envelope works are installed and recorded to support compliance with Building Regulations Part B, BS 9999 / BS 9991 and, for cladding, BS 8414 / BR 135 — with traceable records for the building’s safety case.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Which areas do you cover?</summary><p>We work across London and the South East — including Sussex, Surrey, Kent, Hampshire and Berkshire.</p></details></div></section><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Are you accredited?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"AMPM Building Services works under the accreditations held across AMPM Group, built over the Group's 29-year history. Relevant certificates and PQQ evidence are provided on request."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the golden thread and how do you maintain it?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The golden thread is the digital record of a building's safety information, kept accurate from design through handover as required for higher-risk buildings under the Building Safety Act 2022."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do you work under CDM 2015?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Every project is delivered under the Construction (Design and Management) Regulations 2015."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you complete our PQQ or pre-qualification?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. We hold capability statements, insurances, method statements, accreditations and references ready for PQQ submissions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do you handle fire and building-safety compliance?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Fire-stopping, compartmentation and envelope works are installed and recorded to support compliance with Building Regulations Part B, BS 9999/9991 and, for cladding, BS 8414/BR 135."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which areas do you cover?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"London and the South East, including Sussex, Surrey, Kent, Hampshire and Berkshire."}}]}</script><footer class="foot" data-nav-dark="true"><div class="foot-inner"><div><div class="fwm">AMPM</div><span class="fmer" aria-hidden="true"><span style="background: var(--m-green);"></span><span style="background: var(--m-purple);"></span><span style="background: var(--m-orange);"></span><span style="background: var(--m-blue);"></span></span><p class="ftag">MEPH, Commercial, Fabric and Groundworks — one accountable contractor for London and the South East. The building-services arm of AMPM Group.</p></div><div><h5>Site</h5><ul><li><a href="/">Home</a></li><li><a href="/services/">Services</a></li><li><a href="/work/">Work</a></li><li><a href="/compliance/">Compliance</a></li><li><a href="/about/">About</a></li><li><a href="/contact/">Contact</a></li></ul></div><div><h5>Direct lines</h5><ul><li><a href="mailto:tenders@ampm.co.uk">tenders@ampm.co.uk</a></li><li><a href="mailto:hello@ampm.co.uk">hello@ampm.co.uk</a></li><li><a href="mailto:suppliers@ampm.co.uk">suppliers@ampm.co.uk</a></li><li><a href="mailto:careers@ampm.co.uk">careers@ampm.co.uk</a></li><li><a href="tel:03300430080">0330 043 0080</a></li></ul></div><div><h5>AMPM Group</h5><ul><li><a href="https://ampmgroup.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ampmgroup.co.uk ↗</a></li><li><a href="https://geminiampm.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Gemini AMPM ↗</a></li><li class="muted" style="margin-top: 8px;">AMPM Building Services Ltd</li><li class="muted">A subsidiary of AMPM Group</li><li clas